<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="393" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,433,820]" box="[151,855,433,460]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,433,459]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Description.</emphasis>
Brown with indistinct dark pattern (
<figureCitation box="[705,843,433,460]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–47" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1997,2021]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,535,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-133@11.[174,1412,525,1974]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–47. Macropsis spp., lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404167/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Figs. 34–35</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,433,820]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">
Abdominal apodemes of 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[499,515,469,483]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">nd</superScript>
tergite in male long, with strongly convergent and widened tips (
<figureCitation box="[1258,1425,469,495]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Figs. 183–184</figureCitation>
). Sternal apodemes narrow triangular, separated by angular notch (
<figureCitation box="[890,1057,505,532]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Figs. 185–186</figureCitation>
). Penis stem in side view narrow, usually, bent at almost right angle (
<figureCitation box="[540,705,541,567]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Figs. 187–188</figureCitation>
). 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[737,753,541,555]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">nd</superScript>
valvulae of ovipositor with one very long and narrow preapical tooth each; sometimes one valvula has additional small tooth (
<figureCitation box="[889,987,577,603]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Fig. 189</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
